Jack Howard Richardson (November 18, 1883  November 17, 1957) was an American actor. Born in New York, New York, he was signed to a contract in silent films in 1911 by the Thanhouser Company, where he worked for several years. Richardson appeared in more than 600 films before his death in Santa Barbara, California. 
